#Text=SCHOLASTIC EDUCATION COMBINED WITH

#Text=FREEHOLD FAMILY RESIDENCE,
#Text=SHERBORNE, DORSET.
#Text=TO BE SOLD OR LET,—A Large and Commodioua DWELLING-HOUSE and OFFICES, replete with eTery convenience, situate within its own Grounds, and perfectly secluded, though in the centre of the Town.

#Text=The House is a Modern Villa, pleasantly situated on a handsome lawn, with verandah, pleasure grounds, and shrubberies, productive walled garden, summerhouse, excellent vinery, and forcing house Ac.
#Text=It contains 15 rooms—vis., 4 sitting, 9 bed, and 2 dressing-rooms, with closets, strongroom, pantries, kitchens, larder, and spacious cellars.
#Text=Adjoining is the yard with double coachhouse, stabling for 4 horses, loft, and man servant’s-room over.
#Text=There are also 11 Freehold Cottages and Yards, &c., adjoining, and a Leasehold Walled Garden, to be sold with or without the above.
#Text=Sherborne is a First Class Station on the direct London and Exeter Bailway, and in communication by rail with Weymouth, Bath, and all parts of tne West of England.
#Text=It is renowned for its Abbey Church, Park, and Hoyal Foundation School, at which residents sons receive a firstrate education for the small annual payment of six guineas.
#Text=Sherborne is also the head quarters of the famed Blackmoor Vale Hunt, and within reach of Mr.
#Text=Radclyffe’s and Lord Poltimore’s Hounds.
#Text=For particulars and terms, and to view the Premises, apply to Mr.

#Text=CHURCHEa, CHAPELS, AND FAMILIES.
#Text=EOR SALE,—A well-toned BARREL ORGAN, with DRUM and TRIANGLE, having one Barrel set to Sacred Music, and Two to Waltzes, Airs, &c., for domestic recreation.
#Text=The above Organ is well adapted for a Small Church or Chapel.
#Text=The two last named Barrels could be reset to Sacred Music at a trifling cost.
#Text=The original cost of this Organ was £5O, and is now to be Sold at a considerable reduction.
